 Seawater and carbonate system quantities (molality basis)
 ---------------------------------------------------------

 The results printed in this file are common quantities related to the
 carbonate system, and stoichiometric dissociation or formation constants
 (see the manual for definitions). Quantities related to the solution phase
 are all on a molality basis: moles per kg of pure water solvent.

 Quantities that cannot be calculated for the current solution, because some
 required solute species are not present, are assigned a missing value code
 of 99.0.

